<subSubSection id="2DD56497FFF0FFBDFF20FE1D633520CC" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" type="description">
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF0FFBDFF20FE1D6191228C" blockId="4.[151,692,366,429]" box="[151,404,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">
(
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFF28FE1D6136228C" box="[159,307,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Figs. 2. A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFE89FE1D6189228C" box="[318,396,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">4. A–F</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF0FFBDFF20FE55635922D4" blockId="4.[151,1437,475,1005]" box="[151,860,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF0FFBDFF20FE55614622D4" bold="true" box="[151,323,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Measurement.</emphasis>
Length of male including tegmen: 3.8–4.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF0FFBDFF70FE7061022188" blockId="4.[151,1437,475,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF0FFBDFF70FE70614A2139" bold="true" box="[199,335,510,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Coloration.</emphasis>
Vertex orange, covered with dark brown reticulation; eyes grey with brown transverse stripe; ocelli yellowish brown (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFEDEFDAD61C0211C" box="[361,453,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Face black (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFDDDFDAD62CD211C" box="[618,712,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum pale orange, marked with dark brown reticulation. Scutellum orange with dark brown reticulation, spots on the end of the transverse dark brown (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFB73FDC965182140" box="[1220,1309,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Forewing subhyaline, with many false veins consisting of dark pigment lines; five apical cells with small black brown spots (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFF17FD0160FF2188" box="[160,250,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF0FFBDFF70FD3D62F72034" blockId="4.[151,1437,475,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF0FFBDFF70FD3D616421EC" bold="true" box="[199,353,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Morphology.</emphasis>
Head declivous, including eyes nearly as broad as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFB8BFD3D64C221EC" box="[1084,1223,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Figs. 2B, C</figureCitation>
). Postclypeus flat; anteclypeus ridged medially, truncate at apex (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFD25FD5962ED21D0" box="[658,744,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum length 1.5 times medial length of crown. Scutellum length 0.8 times medial length of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFD3AFD7562E12034" box="[653,740,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF0FFBDFF70FC91633520CC" blockId="4.[151,1437,475,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF0FFBDFF70FC9161792019" bold="true" box="[199,380,798,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with short and long macrosetae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFBDCFC9164CC2018" box="[1131,1225,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular. Subgenital plate triangular-shaped, longer than length of pygofer distinctly, on ventral side with scattered macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFF17FCE960FE20A0" box="[160,251,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
,). Style apex cheliform, lateral margin sinuate, preapical lobe with several setae near inner margin (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFAD8FCE960B92084" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Connective ‘Y’-shaped, similar in length to style (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFD44FC0563492084" box="[755,844,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus dorso-ventrally flattened, dorsal apodeme well-developed, preatrium reduced, shaft curved caudo-dorsally, with triangular lateral processes apically, processes with finely serrated margins; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF0FFBDFD14FC5D632620CC" box="[675,803,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436">Figs. 4E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="31B06794FFF0FFBDFF20F8B360ED2458" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="436" startId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" targetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" targetPageId="4">
