<subSubSection id="2DD56497FFF1FFBCFF70FF1861A023F4" pageId="5" pageNumber="437" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF1FFBCFF70FF1861A023F4" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF1FFBCFF70FF1861472391" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="437">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of this genus by the flattened aedeagus with triangular lobes at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DD56497FFF1FFBCFF70FF516100223C" pageId="5" pageNumber="437" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF1FFBCFF70FF516100223C" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF1FFBCFF70FF51614B23D8" bold="true" box="[199,334,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="437">Etymology.</emphasis>
